1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:06,920
Because you're still useful to me, Lasor.

2
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,479
<i>Sam pa jit cha mi, mi cha jit pa sam.</i>

3
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:11,240
<i>Your body is mine now.</i>

4
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:13,760
<i>All that remains is the last fragment</i>
<i>of your spirit waiting to be extinguished.</i>

5
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:16,360
And I will possess your body forever.

6
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:18,280
His eyes, his behaviors,

7
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:19,920
it's like he's not the same Lasor.

8
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,840
Get out of my son's body now.

9
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:23,200
It's time…

10
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:25,800
…you paid for what you did to me.

11
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:28,400
<i>Om, destruction, great destruction.</i>

12
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:30,560
<i>I curse you into madness, I--</i>

13
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:32,160
Hang in there, Wad.

14
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,480
Only Wan Phat Nang Chi

15
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,320
can purge the dark sorcery from you.

16
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:39,640
In this world, if something can be done,

17
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:41,120
it can be undone.

18
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,480
The astral projection spell.

19
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:44,240
That's dangerous, Wad.

20
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:47,440
Only Old Master Khrua Phut
can save my son.

21
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:56,280
<i>The spell of astral projection</i>

22
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:59,440
<i>is the movement of the subtle body</i>
<i>from the physical body</i>

23
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:02,120
<i>to another realm.</i>

24
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:08,640
<i>You must find Old Master Khrua Phut</i>

25
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:11,880
<i>before this coconut shell sinks.</i>

26
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:15,360
<i>Otherwise, your body will slowly decay,</i>

27
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:17,920
<i>and you will never return to it.</i>

28
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,280
There you are, Wad.

29
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,080
Old Master.

30
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:35,880
Old Master,

31
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:39,400
please save my son from Petch.

32
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:42,000
Your son and Petch

33
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:44,520
are bound by karma.

34
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,120
The time has come

35
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:52,320
for them to bear
the consequences of their past deeds.

36
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:55,080
Knowing this,

37
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:58,720
why would you
throw yourself into their karma?

38
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,280
No parent

39
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:05,240
can stand by while their child suffers.

40
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:08,000
Lasor became like this

41
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:10,760
because I failed to raise him well.

42
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:16,320
Let me pay for it

43
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,560
with my life.

44
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,320
How can I separate Petch's spirit

45
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,440
from Lasor's body?

46
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:38,600
Come back, Wad.

47
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:45,640
Wad!

48
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,080
Come back!

49
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,360
I'm a police officer.

50
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:05,160
Why am I digging dirt?

51
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:09,520
I'm clearing land to grow medicinal herbs.

52
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,760
So I can treat the villagers

53
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:13,640
and spare them expensive medical fees

54
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:16,720
while we wait
for Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet's reply.

55
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:20,560
So are you a village chief
or a doctor, Yiam?

56
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,080
Why not both?

57
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:26,760
I want to care for
the people of Khuan Phra-ngam

58
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,680
like my father did.

59
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:32,760
You already have sorcery

60
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:35,160
and the Klaikot Lek Lai.

61
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:37,880
No bandit would dare enter your district,

62
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:39,280
Khun Yod Phithak.

63
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,280
Sorcery can stop bandits.

64
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,320
It can't stop poverty.

65
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:49,080
That's why I want the villagers
to earn a living on their own.

66
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:51,480
Only then will Khuan Phra-ngam
be peaceful again.

67
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:53,640
Hey, Chang.

68
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:57,440
Right now, Yiam's a village chief.

69
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:59,360
One day, he'll be governor.

70
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:00,440
You're right.

71
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:02,000
Alright, that's enough.

72
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:06,480
It's noon.

73
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,760
Let's eat.

74
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:14,400
So what did you cook today?

75
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:18,840
Fried eggs? Boiled eggs? Steamed eggs?

76
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:22,800
None of those. I tried something new.

77
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,080
What is it?

78
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,880
Son-in-Law Eggs

79
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:39,280
Even if I had eggs every single meal,

80
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:41,920
if it's your cooking,

81
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,280
I'd eat until my face turned into one.

82
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,200
How did Yiam

83
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:52,320
tame a fierce tigress like you

84
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:55,200
into a tiny kitten?

85
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,800
My dad once said,

86
00:06:57,880 --> 00:07:00,720
"If you want to live, respect your wife."

87
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,400
Fair enough.

88
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:24,120
Seeing torch ginger

89
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:27,840
reminds me of when we first met.

90
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:31,280
Have you heard
the legend of the torch ginger?

91
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:38,760
They say there was once
a man and a woman deeply in love.

92
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:42,760
But the woman's father opposed them,
so they couldn't be together.

93
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:44,680
Before they parted,

94
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:48,080
the young man promised
he would return to take her away.

95
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:52,720
The woman waited and waited with hope,

96
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:55,800
day after day,

97
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:58,280
until she withered away in sorrow.

98
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:01,320
Before she died,

99
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:04,280
she prayed to be reborn
as a torch ginger flower,

100
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:07,760
so she could wait for her beloved forever.

101
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:14,560
Why must the legend end so sadly?

102
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,320
It's not fair.

103
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:20,200
They loved each other
but couldn't be together.

104
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:26,800
Fortunately, you and I

105
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:29,840
aren't that unlucky.

106
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:32,799
Otherwise,

107
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:34,720
I might be the one dying of heartbreak.

108
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:39,280
Then if you turned into a torch ginger,

109
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:42,480
I'd eat you every single day.

110
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:44,880
Really?

111
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:56,160
Dad. Uncle Chaem.

112
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:03,960
We'd like to stay a night or two.
Would that be alright?

113
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:06,120
Of course.

114
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:09,920
You're my father-in-law.
Stay as long as you wish.

115
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:15,400
Dad, have you finished
cleansing Lasor's sorcery?

116
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:19,960
It's done.

117
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:23,280
Then I'll prepare your bedding.

118
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:26,520
I'll help.

119
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,760
No, I'll do it myself.

120
00:09:29,680 --> 00:09:31,480
You stay and talk with your father-in-law.

121
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:43,120
Yiam,

122
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,720
I have something important
to discuss with you.

123
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,400
I need to ask a favor.

124
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:59,000
Tell me.

125
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:01,560
If there's anything I can do, I'm willing.

126
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:05,560
Can I ask you for the Klaikot Lek Lai?

127
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,920
How can I separate Petch's spirit

128
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,960
from Lasor's body?

129
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:19,040
Only the Klaikot Lek Lai

130
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:21,280
has the power

131
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:24,520
to divide an evil spirit from a pure one.

132
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:28,720
How?

133
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:33,280
Good and evil are like oil and water.

134
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:37,520
Even in the same vessel,
they cannot merge.

135
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,680
The Klaikot Lek Lai

136
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:43,920
was forged by a hermit
of great spiritual attainment.

137
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:46,920
It was created to destroy evil

138
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,720
and protect virtue.

139
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:54,800
So

140
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,920
if Lasor truly repents
and returns to goodness,

141
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:02,280
no one else will have to suffer,
is that right?

142
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,320
I know

143
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:15,680
that without the Klaikot Lek Lai,

144
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:18,760
you'll lose your sorcery.

145
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,280
What do you need it for?

146
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:43,600
I must use it
to settle matters from the past.

147
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:49,560
What matters? Can you tell me?

148
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:54,320
I can't tell you yet.

149
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:07,640
Let me speak with Yiwha first.

150
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,600
No.

151
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:13,320
Yiwha must not know.

152
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:17,760
I don't want her dragged into this again.

153
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:22,360
I want her to live as an ordinary person.

154
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:28,360
Yiam, I'm begging you. Help me.

155
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:49,880
How was it? Did it work?

156
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,680
Yiam asked for time.

157
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:55,680
Lasor's life

158
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:59,120
now rests in his hands.

159
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:08,120
Let's hope he shows mercy.

160
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:32,600
I know

161
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:36,840
Dad came to ask for your Lek Lai.

162
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,240
It's yours.

163
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:47,560
If you refuse, I won't blame you.

164
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:54,320
What does he need it for?

165
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,160
If it weren't important,

166
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:01,720
he wouldn't have asked.

167
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:07,880
Important enough
not to tell me, his own daughter?

168
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:11,320
He told me nothing.

169
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:17,400
Only that he must use it
to settle something from the past.

170
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:22,200
Settle the past?

171
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:26,400
Or…

172
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:41,640
<i>Sattha dhanung!</i>

173
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,560
Show yourself.

174
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,360
Why hide, Petch?

175
00:14:56,840 --> 00:15:01,280
I thought the sorcery centipede
had already killed you.

176
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:05,680
Your petty tricks won't kill me.

177
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:10,280
Step out of my son's body

178
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:12,480
and face me.

179
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:15,840
Go on. Go ahead, Wad.

180
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:18,160
Kill me.

181
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:22,720
Even Yod, with his sacred tattoo,

182
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:26,080
was pierced

183
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:28,600
by a bamboo spear.

184
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:33,120
It's your turn to join him in hell.

185
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:41,080
- Ugh!
- Come on!

186
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:43,280
Go on, Wad.

187
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:46,080
Kill your own son.

188
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:51,800
You don't dare, do you?

189
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:15,480
Wad. Wad.

190
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:20,920
No, Yiam.

191
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:23,760
Good.

192
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:30,040
All of you together.

193
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:33,520
I'll send you all

194
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:37,040
to hell at once.

195
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:43,000
<i>Om, twist, great twist.</i>
<i>I will twist your liver</i>

196
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:45,440
<i>and your lungs.</i>

197
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:46,640
<i>I will twist your outer organs.</i>

198
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:47,680
Ugh!

199
00:16:47,760 --> 00:16:50,600
<i>I will twist your inner organs.</i>
<i>I will twist your heart.</i>

200
00:16:50,680 --> 00:16:52,440
<i>Om prasitti swaha,</i>

201
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:53,800
<i>swa--</i>

202
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:04,920
My heart!

203
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:05,920
Yiwha!

204
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:10,200
Wad.

205
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,119
Lasor!

206
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,400
Yiwha!

207
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:17,760
Yiwha.

208
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:32,920
Their hearts are connected.

209
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,600
I should never have miscalculated.

210
00:18:18,320 --> 00:18:20,080
Come back to me, Yiwha…

211
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:54,040
Lasor…

212
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:57,520
Yiwha…

213
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:10,960
Phraya Kaipetch

214
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:13,480
has left your body, hasn't he?

215
00:19:13,560 --> 00:19:14,800
Not yet.

216
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:19,640
He's only unconscious.
That's why my spirit can come out.

217
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:22,120
But when the shadow swallows the moon,

218
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:25,080
my soul will shatter

219
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,800
and he will take my body forever.

220
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,760
I'll help you.

221
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:37,840
I'll kill Phraya Kaipetch
before that day comes.

222
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:41,040
Kaipetch and I
share the same heart, Yiwha.

223
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,440
If you kill him,

224
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:46,000
you will die with him.

225
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:01,600
We only have each other.

226
00:20:02,520 --> 00:20:04,720
If anything happens to you,

227
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:09,080
I might as well be dead.

228
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,600
You must stay strong.

229
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:15,720
We'll find a way
to destroy Phraya Kaipetch.

230
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:19,120
Thank you, Yiwha,

231
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:22,640
for making me strong again.

232
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:25,720
I'll fight beside you

233
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:28,320
to bring Phraya Kaipetch down.

234
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:57,640
Yiwha.

235
00:20:58,160 --> 00:21:00,320
Father Wad, Yiwha's awake.

236
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:03,920
Yiwha.

237
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:13,400
You know what?

238
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:18,400
You were unconscious for three days
and three nights. We were so worried.

239
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:21,440
I wasn't sure

240
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:23,800
the twin-lotus pollen pill would work.

241
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:27,880
Dad…

242
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:33,560
while I was asleep,
I saw Lasor in my dream.

243
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:36,120
How was he?

244
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:53,640
This is why

245
00:21:55,320 --> 00:21:57,040
you want the Lek Lai, isn't it?

246
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:03,560
Old Master Khrua Phut told me
to forge it into a sacred dagger

247
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:06,720
to destroy Petch inside Lasor's body.

248
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:10,960
And what about Yiwha?

249
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:14,360
How can you be sure she'll be safe?

250
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:18,600
The Klaikot Lek Lai

251
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:21,520
destroys evil and protects good.

252
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:24,360
If Lasor can truly change,

253
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:26,720
Yiwha won't be harmed.

254
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:33,040
And if he doesn't?

255
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:36,120
What happens to her then?

256
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:48,080
Then I cannot give you the Lek Lai
to destroy Phraya Kaipetch.

257
00:23:35,520 --> 00:23:37,840
Kaipetch and I
share the same heart, Yiwha.

258
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:40,360
If you kill him,

259
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:42,720
you will die with him.

260
00:23:52,680 --> 00:23:53,960
Yiwha, what are you doing?

261
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:58,480
Well…

262
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:01,000
I…

263
00:24:02,160 --> 00:24:03,800
I just thought

264
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:07,400
maybe this would free

265
00:24:07,960 --> 00:24:09,200
Lasor's spirit.

266
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:10,960
There must be another way.

267
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:14,560
Even if you're willing to die,

268
00:24:15,360 --> 00:24:16,960
Phraya Kaipetch

269
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:20,120
could simply move to another body.

270
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:23,480
Trust me. Don't do this.

271
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,280
Then what do you want me to do?

272
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:29,120
Just wait for Lasor's spirit to shatter

273
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,160
without doing anything?

274
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:56,160
You don't have to do anything.

275
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,760
I'll do it for you.

276
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:32,640
Father Wad.

277
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:41,400
I will give you the Klaikot Lek Lai.

278
00:26:02,320 --> 00:26:03,560
I've thought it through.

279
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:06,880
Only the Klaikot Lek Lai

280
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:09,480
can destroy Phraya Kaipetch completely.

281
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:14,400
But now the Lek Lai
has fused with your body.

282
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:17,920
Removing it won't be easy.

283
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:21,400
It will be painful.

284
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:26,720
I'd rather suffer the pain

285
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:29,480
than watch the people I love suffer.

286
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:44,760
I was right

287
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:48,400
to entrust Yiwha to you.

288
00:26:59,880 --> 00:27:02,840
Tell me what I must do.

289
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:26,640
Dad said once the Lek Lai is summoned,

290
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:31,920
all your spells and sorcery
will leave with it.

291
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,560
After this,

292
00:27:33,640 --> 00:27:37,240
you'll be an ordinary man
with no powers at all.

293
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:41,920
Are you certain?

294
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:51,680
If it can destroy Phraya Kaipetch
inside your brother's body,

295
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:54,680
isn't it worth it?

296
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:03,640
Thank you so much

297
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:06,440
for doing this for me.

298
00:28:07,480 --> 00:28:08,920
It's not just the Lek Lai.

299
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:12,800
I'd even give

300
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:16,600
my life to you.

301
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:06,440
<i>Putthomenatho</i>

302
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:08,720
<i>Dammomenatho</i>

303
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:10,680
<i>Sanghomenatho</i>

304
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:19,440
<i>Sakaphacha bucha cha mahabucha…</i>

305
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:08,320
Yiam.

306
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:10,480
Yiam.

307
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:19,480
It's eating the honey.

308
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:33,520
- Ugh!
- Hey.

309
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:34,840
Chang.

310
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:38,800
It's gone.

311
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:50,640
Please hear me.

312
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:55,680
Please help us defeat evil.

313
00:30:57,840 --> 00:30:59,080
I beg you.

314
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:13,400
Hey.

315
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,000
It came back.

316
00:31:36,280 --> 00:31:37,960
Doesn't it burn, Yiwha?

317
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:41,680
The Klaikot Lek Lai chooses its owner.

318
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:46,560
Only one with merit

319
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:49,000
and virtue may hold it.

320
00:31:50,720 --> 00:31:54,080
You've been chosen, Yiwha.

321
00:31:54,160 --> 00:31:57,160
What do we do now?

322
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:59,120
I'll forge it into a dagger

323
00:32:00,320 --> 00:32:03,120
to destroy Petch inside Lasor.

324
00:32:04,760 --> 00:32:08,800
Forging the Lek Lai dagger
requires not only alchemical knowledge,

325
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:14,040
but must be done at an auspicious time.

326
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:18,160
Only on Tuesday or Saturday.
Only then will it gain its full power.

327
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:21,880
This Saturday,
the fifth day of the waxing moon,

328
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:23,640
is an auspicious hour.

329
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:02,960
Yiam, how are you?

330
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:20,720
I'm fine.

331
00:33:23,520 --> 00:33:26,200
What about the Lek Lai? Did we get it?

332
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:41,720
It's here.

333
00:33:46,400 --> 00:33:48,280
The Lek Lai is yours now.

334
00:33:49,640 --> 00:33:51,200
Take good care of it.

335
00:33:56,240 --> 00:33:57,920
I'm only borrowing it.

336
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:01,880
When this is over,
I'll return it to you, Yiam.

337
00:34:01,960 --> 00:34:03,840
As long as you're safe,

338
00:34:05,640 --> 00:34:07,360
I need nothing else.

339
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:36,800
Lasor,

340
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:41,199
when the shadow swallows the moon,
your body

341
00:34:41,719 --> 00:34:44,800
and heart will be mine.

342
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:47,120
Wad and Yiam

343
00:34:47,639 --> 00:34:49,639
cannot stop me.

344
00:34:58,640 --> 00:35:01,360
I wonder how Lasor is.

345
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:03,440
He'll be fine

346
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:08,760
as long as Phraya Kaipetch
hasn't fully merged with him.

347
00:35:14,520 --> 00:35:16,080
Yiam,

348
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:20,520
If Dad uses the Lek Lai dagger
to destroy Phraya Kaipetch,

349
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:25,400
will my brother survive?

350
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:28,640
Are you afraid the Lek Lai dagger

351
00:35:30,600 --> 00:35:33,720
will kill your brother
along with Phraya Kaipetch?

352
00:35:38,880 --> 00:35:42,680
If Lasor truly repents, he'll be safe.

353
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:46,560
Like Angulimala,

354
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:50,720
he once lost his way,
but after turning back to the Dhamma,

355
00:35:50,800 --> 00:35:53,200
he attained arahantship.

356
00:35:54,720 --> 00:35:57,000
Karma is always just.

357
00:35:59,640 --> 00:36:02,280
The Dhamma protects the righteous.

358
00:36:22,160 --> 00:36:23,240
What are you thinking about?

359
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:26,560
Grandma Chi Pa Khao's last prophecy.

360
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:31,200
Your son will bring
great ruin upon Chum Suea.

361
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:33,960
And last, your daughter

362
00:36:34,040 --> 00:36:36,320
will lead death to her father.

363
00:36:41,120 --> 00:36:43,840
What happened in the past
might have just been coincidence.

364
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:46,800
The future

365
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:49,480
is beyond our sight.

366
00:36:49,560 --> 00:36:54,080
If you cling to prophecy,
you'll only create suffering.

367
00:36:54,160 --> 00:36:56,280
I've already lost Panan once.

368
00:36:58,080 --> 00:36:59,760
I will not lose my children too.

369
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:04,600
Whatever the price, I will pay it.

370
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:01,920
<i>Om, awaken, great awakening.</i>

371
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:05,240
<i>I'll awaken the corpse-crows</i>
<i>with</i> ahang tukang.

372
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:06,520
<i>Namaphatha.</i>

373
00:39:11,640 --> 00:39:14,160
Go destroy their Lek Lai forging ritual.

374
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:16,040
Go!

375
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:30,080
Petch has sent corpse-crows
to stop the ritual.

376
00:39:31,520 --> 00:39:32,560
Keep hammering.

377
00:39:34,440 --> 00:39:37,120
I said keep hammering. Don't look at it!

378
00:39:53,240 --> 00:39:54,480
I'll fight this.

379
00:39:54,560 --> 00:39:55,960
But you no longer have sorcery.

380
00:39:56,040 --> 00:39:57,720
Even without sorcery,

381
00:39:57,800 --> 00:39:59,800
I still have the swordsmanship
my father taught me.

382
00:40:01,880 --> 00:40:02,840
Yiam.

383
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:04,720
I've got a gun.

384
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:07,640
Yiam, wait for me.

385
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:13,120
Wait for me too!

386
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:15,480
Noree, stay here.

387
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:17,440
I'll help them.

388
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:25,240
Hold this for me.

389
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:48,640
It's done.

390
00:41:54,120 --> 00:41:55,080
Yiwha.

391
00:41:58,120 --> 00:41:59,320
Stab its heart.

392
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:26,920
Damn it!

393
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:29,880
Let's see

394
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:32,360
how long you can keep
running from death, Wad!

395
00:42:41,760 --> 00:42:45,400
This dagger holds far greater power
than I imagined.

396
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:49,000
The Klaikot Lek Lai, forged together with
all my spells and sacred incantations,

397
00:42:50,240 --> 00:42:54,320
has become more potent than any weapon.

398
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:56,720
Then why didn't you use it

399
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:58,960
on that animated crow yourself?

400
00:43:00,240 --> 00:43:01,920
I am but a forest bandit.

401
00:43:02,680 --> 00:43:04,640
I cannot wield a sacred weapon like this.

402
00:43:05,760 --> 00:43:06,920
The Lek Lai dagger

403
00:43:08,600 --> 00:43:10,680
reveals its true power

404
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:16,000
only in the hands of its rightful owner.

405
00:43:21,720 --> 00:43:25,880
This dagger belongs to
someone pure of heart like you, Yiwha.

406
00:43:32,120 --> 00:43:36,360
By now, Petch must know our plan.

407
00:43:36,880 --> 00:43:40,640
A vile man like him
won't surrender easily.

408
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:54,720
Yiwha.

409
00:43:56,160 --> 00:43:57,320
Drink some water, Dad.

410
00:43:58,400 --> 00:43:59,960
It's late. Why aren't you asleep?

411
00:44:01,520 --> 00:44:05,320
Well, I can't.

412
00:44:05,400 --> 00:44:08,160
My thoughts won't rest.

413
00:44:09,440 --> 00:44:13,280
Thinking won't change fate.
No one knows what tomorrow brings.

414
00:44:16,200 --> 00:44:17,040
Dad,

415
00:44:18,280 --> 00:44:21,000
if we save Lasor,

416
00:44:21,520 --> 00:44:24,080
let's return to Chum Suea.

417
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:27,840
Don't send him away.

418
00:44:28,480 --> 00:44:30,320
If we go back,

419
00:44:30,400 --> 00:44:34,160
you could conceal the mountain again
with your illusions.

420
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:37,240
No one would ever find us.

421
00:44:37,840 --> 00:44:39,000
And Yiam?

422
00:44:41,360 --> 00:44:43,920
Can you truly leave your husband?

423
00:44:51,640 --> 00:44:53,200
Stop thinking about this.

424
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:57,040
You're about to live an ordinary life,

425
00:44:57,560 --> 00:44:59,440
as an ordinary woman.

426
00:45:00,840 --> 00:45:03,800
You shouldn't return to Chum Suea again.

427
00:45:05,640 --> 00:45:07,080
Go to sleep, Yiwha.

428
00:45:51,720 --> 00:45:53,320
Father Wad's medicine works wonders.

429
00:45:54,040 --> 00:45:56,560
My wounds are nearly healed.

430
00:46:00,360 --> 00:46:01,560
Yiam,

431
00:46:02,280 --> 00:46:06,200
if one day I'm no longer here,
how would you live?

432
00:46:07,600 --> 00:46:09,160
Where would you go?

433
00:46:11,600 --> 00:46:16,080
I'm just asking. Life is uncertain.

434
00:46:16,720 --> 00:46:18,200
No one knows

435
00:46:18,880 --> 00:46:22,120
whether tomorrow
we'll still stand side by side.

436
00:46:26,680 --> 00:46:31,800
Today, tomorrow, in this life or the next,

437
00:46:32,960 --> 00:46:35,560
I will follow you and love you, Yiwha.

438
00:46:37,720 --> 00:46:39,800
I'd even swear it before the Buddha.

439
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:41,520
No need.

440
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:45,560
I believe you.

441
00:46:47,360 --> 00:46:51,560
Words matter less than what you've done.

442
00:46:52,640 --> 00:46:55,160
And everything you've done for me

443
00:46:59,000 --> 00:47:01,520
has already proven

444
00:47:02,200 --> 00:47:04,520
how much you love me.

445
00:47:14,000 --> 00:47:15,360
Since you know I love you,

446
00:47:17,720 --> 00:47:19,680
then don't leave me alone.

447
00:47:25,120 --> 00:47:28,400
My dad, my mom,

448
00:47:29,880 --> 00:47:32,960
my sister, they're all gone.

449
00:47:36,360 --> 00:47:39,320
I have no one else but you, Yiwha.

450
00:48:11,320 --> 00:48:13,800
I summoned you all here

451
00:48:13,880 --> 00:48:16,040
to make it clear

452
00:48:16,680 --> 00:48:20,400
that if you become my men,

453
00:48:20,920 --> 00:48:25,000
I will protect you. Rob as you please.

454
00:48:25,080 --> 00:48:28,120
Raid any house you want.

455
00:48:28,200 --> 00:48:31,880
I will neither obstruct nor arrest you.

456
00:48:35,360 --> 00:48:37,240
Are you turning the governor's residence

457
00:48:37,320 --> 00:48:39,360
into a bandit's den, Sir Lasor?

458
00:48:42,880 --> 00:48:44,240
Would you rather remain bandits

459
00:48:45,600 --> 00:48:47,200
or become the governor's men?

460
00:48:48,400 --> 00:48:49,880
If you're my man,

461
00:48:50,640 --> 00:48:52,760
I'll take good care of you.

462
00:48:53,800 --> 00:48:55,520
You won't have to run or hide again.

463
00:48:56,320 --> 00:48:59,960
I'll divide territories among you.
You'll rule them yourselves.

464
00:49:01,200 --> 00:49:02,640
Interested?

465
00:49:03,600 --> 00:49:06,600
Yiam, Village Chief of Khuan Phra-ngam,
and his men

466
00:49:06,680 --> 00:49:10,680
intend to wipe out land and river bandits,

467
00:49:10,760 --> 00:49:12,920
just as his father,
Khun Yod Pakdee, once did.

468
00:49:14,040 --> 00:49:16,840
If we let them continue,

469
00:49:16,920 --> 00:49:20,320
your dens will be destroyed.

470
00:49:21,120 --> 00:49:23,800
Nothing comes without a price.

471
00:49:23,880 --> 00:49:27,480
What do you want from us, Sir Lasor?

472
00:49:39,880 --> 00:49:41,840
I only want the Lek Lai dagger.

473
00:49:42,960 --> 00:49:44,920
Whoever brings it to me,

474
00:49:45,000 --> 00:49:48,200
along with Yiam's head
and his companions',

475
00:49:48,280 --> 00:49:50,280
will be appointed

476
00:49:51,200 --> 00:49:53,640
the next Village Chief of Khuan Phra-ngam.

477
00:50:14,560 --> 00:50:15,440
Yiam!

478
00:50:15,520 --> 00:50:16,480
Yiwha, run!

479
00:50:16,560 --> 00:50:18,480
Come here!

480
00:50:24,160 --> 00:50:25,640
Yiam!

481
00:50:32,800 --> 00:50:34,080
Yiam.

482
00:50:35,400 --> 00:50:36,480
Are you alright?

483
00:50:37,840 --> 00:50:38,800
Noree.

484
00:50:39,320 --> 00:50:40,520
Noree.

485
00:50:49,320 --> 00:50:50,240
Noree, run.

486
00:50:51,280 --> 00:50:52,120
Chang.

487
00:50:53,480 --> 00:50:54,520
Are you alright?

488
00:50:56,760 --> 00:50:58,160
Pun.

489
00:51:14,480 --> 00:51:15,600
- Hey!
- Oh.

490
00:51:28,720 --> 00:51:29,560
Yiam, go!

491
00:51:29,640 --> 00:51:30,640
Let's go.

492
00:51:34,920 --> 00:51:36,040
Hey!

493
00:52:08,240 --> 00:52:12,040
<i>Matiyano matiya matithi sodhaya sapasa</i>

494
00:52:12,120 --> 00:52:13,920
<i>nomana thenasa.</i>

495
00:52:21,120 --> 00:52:22,160
Yiam.

496
00:52:27,120 --> 00:52:28,480
Petch must have sent them.

497
00:52:31,240 --> 00:52:32,280
The Lek Lai dagger.

498
00:52:52,960 --> 00:52:54,480
How beautiful.

499
00:52:55,200 --> 00:52:57,120
No wonder Sir Lasor wants it.

500
00:53:14,840 --> 00:53:17,800
Worth the trip, I'd say.

501
00:53:17,880 --> 00:53:21,760
A fine weapon and a fine woman.

502
00:53:23,880 --> 00:53:24,960
Yiam.

503
00:53:42,520 --> 00:53:43,760
Ugh!

504
00:54:06,720 --> 00:54:08,040
Petch knows now.

505
00:54:09,600 --> 00:54:11,400
That's why he sent men
to seize the dagger.

506
00:54:13,240 --> 00:54:15,920
We protected it this time,

507
00:54:16,440 --> 00:54:19,360
but we don't know when he'll strike again.

508
00:54:20,120 --> 00:54:21,640
There are so few of us.

509
00:54:22,720 --> 00:54:24,600
How can we possibly fight
his entire bandit force?

510
00:54:26,440 --> 00:54:28,720
I'll ask my friends from the police unit.

511
00:54:29,400 --> 00:54:32,640
The police unit
is filled with Phraya Kaipetch's men.

512
00:54:33,480 --> 00:54:34,640
Who would help you?

513
00:54:41,320 --> 00:54:43,080
There are people heading this way.

514
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:45,960
Who are they?

515
00:54:50,080 --> 00:54:52,520
Hem? Khem?

516
00:54:52,600 --> 00:54:53,920
How did you get here?

517
00:54:54,440 --> 00:54:57,800
We heard you'd returned
to Khuan Phra-ngam, so we came.

518
00:54:57,880 --> 00:55:01,440
We can never repay you
for what you did for us.

519
00:55:01,520 --> 00:55:03,760
I'll gather more men.

520
00:55:03,840 --> 00:55:05,680
Thank you both

521
00:55:06,720 --> 00:55:08,360
for standing ready
to live and die with me.

522
00:55:17,160 --> 00:55:19,680
I hear the people Wad once helped

523
00:55:19,760 --> 00:55:21,320
have joined Yiam's force.

524
00:55:21,400 --> 00:55:24,000
Hey. They're just ordinary villagers.

525
00:55:24,080 --> 00:55:25,920
They're no match for you.

526
00:55:26,000 --> 00:55:29,040
But Yiam and the bandit
both wield powerful sorcery.

527
00:55:29,120 --> 00:55:32,600
If we fight them,
we'll lose again and again.

528
00:55:32,680 --> 00:55:34,640
That's right. We're withdrawing.

529
00:55:35,520 --> 00:55:38,360
Hey, hey. Calm down.

530
00:55:40,400 --> 00:55:44,360
You don't need to worry.
I already have a way to defeat them.

531
00:55:47,280 --> 00:55:48,840
The water in this basin

532
00:55:48,920 --> 00:55:51,000
is Muak Pha water.

533
00:55:51,600 --> 00:55:52,640
Muak Pha water?

534
00:55:52,720 --> 00:55:56,600
Holy water from the peak
of Khao Phrom, an elixir.

535
00:55:56,680 --> 00:55:58,880
Drink it, and you'll be invulnerable.
No blade or spear can pierce you.

536
00:55:58,960 --> 00:56:01,720
Not even the Lek Lai dagger.

537
00:56:02,640 --> 00:56:03,880
Muak Pha water?

538
00:56:04,920 --> 00:56:06,120
Where did you get it?

539
00:56:06,200 --> 00:56:08,680
Old Master Khrua Phut gave it to me.

540
00:56:09,280 --> 00:56:12,240
But there's only a little. If you're
too slow, you'll miss your chance.

541
00:56:12,320 --> 00:56:13,280
- Hey.
- Hurry up.

542
00:56:13,360 --> 00:56:14,920
- I want it.
- I want it too.

543
00:56:15,000 --> 00:56:16,240
Let me drink first.

544
00:56:16,320 --> 00:56:17,240
Hey.

545
00:56:20,840 --> 00:56:23,760
The more you drink,
the stronger you'll become.

546
00:56:23,840 --> 00:56:24,720
Oh.

547
00:56:24,800 --> 00:56:26,000
Muak Pha water.

548
00:56:37,800 --> 00:56:40,600
This isn't Muak Pha water!

549
00:56:42,200 --> 00:56:45,080
It's ash-water
from the bones of vengeful spirits.

550
00:56:45,160 --> 00:56:46,960
Once you drink it,

551
00:56:47,040 --> 00:56:50,240
you're as good as dead,
so you'll never have to die again.

552
00:56:55,360 --> 00:56:57,280
Come. Rise as my servants.

553
00:57:11,120 --> 00:57:12,560
I'll be waiting to see

554
00:57:14,000 --> 00:57:17,480
how you withstand my army of the dead.

555
00:57:23,520 --> 00:57:26,080
Yiwha's love made me realize

556
00:57:26,160 --> 00:57:28,000
that a heart that forgives

557
00:57:29,120 --> 00:57:31,080
is far lighter
than one that clings to hatred.

558
00:57:31,160 --> 00:57:33,160
I will find a way to save Lasor

559
00:57:34,160 --> 00:57:35,640
and bring down Phraya Kaipetch.

560
00:57:35,720 --> 00:57:38,840
May goodness be the shield
that protects us all.

561
00:57:38,920 --> 00:57:41,000
Please grant us

562
00:57:41,080 --> 00:57:43,120
victory over our enemies.

563
00:57:43,200 --> 00:57:46,400
<i>I'm here. I'm right here.</i>

564
00:57:46,480 --> 00:57:48,720
- Where are we?
- I think

565
00:57:48,800 --> 00:57:50,440
this is the world after death.

566
00:57:51,760 --> 00:57:53,600
He's using a concealment spell.

567
00:57:54,280 --> 00:57:55,400
You must use the Sema-dispelling spell.

568
00:58:50,000 --> 00:58:52,000
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
